cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM

This paper deals with the task of lighting estimation from face images using deep Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The use of deep CNNs and GANs for regression and denoising also suggests that the paper could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves the estimation of intrinsic image decomposition, which could place it in the category of cs.GR (Graphics). Finally, the use of synthetic data for training the network could also suggest the category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
